In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup} (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 5.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @Lime{1}. Trim and remove strings from @Sugar Snap Peas{4%oz} if needed. Trim @Scallions{2}; cut whites into ½-inch-thick pieces and thinly slice greens.

== Creamy Chili Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Sour Cream{1.5%tbsp}, ½ tsp @Sweet Thai Chili Sauce{1%oz}, juice from one lime wedge, and a pinch of @salt{} (for 4 servings, use 1 tsp chili sauce and juice from two lime wedges).

Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

== Stir-Fry ==

Meanwhile, open package of @Chopped Chicken Breast{10%oz} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and almost cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add snap peas and scallion whites to pan and cook, stirring occasionally, until snap peas are tender and chicken is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Remove pan from heat. Add @Hoisin Sauce{2%tbsp}, remaining chili sauce, and @water{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings); stir until everything is thoroughly coated.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in half the scallion greens and as much lime zest as you like.

Divide rice between bowls and top with stir-fry. Drizzle with creamy chili sauce and sprinkle with remaining scallion greens. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.